  <title>Cogl.Snippet.prototype.set_declarations</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function set_declarations(declarations: String): void {
    // Gjs wrapper for cogl_snippet_set_declarations()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Sets a source string that will be inserted in the global scope of
the generated shader when this snippet is used on a pipeline. This
string is typically used to declare uniforms, attributes or
functions that will be used by the other parts of the snippets.</p>  <p>This function should only be called before the snippet is attached
to its first pipeline. After that the snippet should be considered
immutable.</p>
  <p>Since 1.10</p>
